        "text": "ḥérem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") was an archaic institution, often alluded to in the OT. A city or nation that was hostile to Jehovah was ‘banned,’ or ‘devoted’ (etymologically, as Arabic shews, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
